Title: ARPANET Project Notes
Description.note: The ARPANET Project Notes collection includes documentation created at or housed by the Network Measurement Center at UCLA, including ARPANET Satellite System (ASS) Notes, notes on packet radio (i.e. Packet Radio Temp Notes), and SPADE admin notes. These all document the development and use of the first Interface Message Processor (IMP)––which functioned similar to a router in today's internet infrastructure––within the world's first large-scale packet-switching network (ARPANET), by UCLA computer scientists and engineers.
